    "key": "DR",
    "description": "<p>A druid is a Neutral-aligned cleric who dedicates themselves to preserving and balancing nature, transitioning from traditional clerical duties upon reaching 9th level. To become a druid, a cleric must spend 1–4 months meditating in a woodland home under the guidance of a higher-level druid. Druids emphasize harmony with nature and avoid spells or actions tied to Good or Evil.</p><p>Druids have several distinct characteristics:</p><ul><li><strong>Armor and Weapons</strong>: They cannot use metal items, relying on leather armor, wooden shields, and non-metal, non-piercing weapons like staves.</li><li><strong>Living and Philosophy</strong>: Druids must live in a natural setting, caring for and protecting a specific woodland area. They view themselves as stewards of nature, punishing deliberate harm while tolerating minor, necessary disruptions.</li><li><strong>Spells</strong>: Druids can cast clerical spells along with a unique set of nature-oriented spells, including abilities to control plants, predict weather, and summon animals.</li><li><strong>Advancement</strong>: Higher-level druids must challenge and defeat others of equal rank to advance, with only one \"Great Druid\" existing at the 36th level.</li></ul><p>Druids blend magical abilities with a deep commitment to the balance and protection of nature.</p>",
